Rating: 3
To Oakbrook: By "stringy" when you brown the chicken, I assume that the chicken breasts stick to the pan and shred when you try to turn them. If that is indeed the case it could be one of these reasons: (1) you may not be patting your chicken dry (both sides) before you saute it, it will stick if you don't; (2) you may have your heat up too high -- make sure your heat is medium-high not "full blast" high; or (3) you may be putting the chicken into the pan before the oil or butter is fully heated. Also, if you are already doing the three things I mentioned above, you may be turning the chicken before it is ready to be turned, which will cause it to shred. As it is browning, don't move it or keep turning it over to check on it -- instead try lightly pushing it from the side with your tongs (or whatever utensil you use), when it is browned and ready it will "give" and move easily. Quite simply, if it doesn't "give", it isn't browned or ready to turn -- just be patient until you can move it easily. I hope this helps, good luck!

