FOR LOW-FAT FANS: I can give you a low-fat version of this recipe that I have been making for a couple of years. Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper. Melt butter in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken breasts and sauté until cooked through, about 5 minutes per side. Transfer chicken to platter. Tent with aluminum foil to keep warm. Add 1/3 cup shallots to same skillet and sauté 1 minute. Add 1/2 cup of dry white wine and 1/2 cup of chicken stock in pan over medium heat; reduce until about 4-5 tablespoons are left. Add your 2 tablespoons tarragon, 2 tablespoons grainy dijon mustard and 1 tablespoon honey. Stir for a minute or 2 until thickened on LOW heat and add chicken for 3-4 minutes to coat with sauce. Serve. It's a never-fail receipe that my husband loves!

